2. Collections Framework

Collection Hierarchy

Collection
   |
   +-- List
   |      |
   |      +-- ArrayList
   |      +-- LinkedList
   |
   +-- Set
   |      |
   |      +-- HashSet
   |      +-- TreeSet
   |
   +-- Queue
          |
          +-- PriorityQueue

⸻

ArrayList

List<String> customers =
        new ArrayList<>();
customers.add("John");

Characteristics

Ordered
Allows duplicates
Fast reads
Slow middle insertions

⸻

LinkedList

List<String> customers =
        new LinkedList<>();

Characteristics

Fast insertions
Slow random access

⸻

HashSet

Set<String> customers =
        new HashSet<>();

Characteristics

No duplicates
No guaranteed order
O(1) lookup

⸻

HashMap

Most common interview question.

Map<Long, Customer> customers =
        new HashMap<>();
customers.put(1L, customer);

Characteristics

Key/Value
Allows null key
Not thread-safe
O(1) average lookup

⸻

ConcurrentHashMap

Map<Long, Customer> customers =
        new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

Characteristics

Thread-safe
Supports concurrent updates

