3. Streams API

What is a Stream?

Streams process data declaratively.

Traditional:

List<String> results =
        new ArrayList<>();
for(String name : names) {
    if(name.startsWith("J")) {
        results.add(name);
    }
}

Stream:

List<String> results =
        names.stream()
             .filter(name -> name.startsWith("J"))
             .toList();

⸻

Common Operations

Filter

customers.stream()
         .filter(c -> c.isActive());

⸻

Map

customers.stream()
         .map(Customer::getName);

⸻

Sorted

customers.stream()
         .sorted(
             Comparator.comparing(
                 Customer::getName));

⸻

Collect

List<String> names =
        customers.stream()
                 .map(Customer::getName)
                 .toList();

⸻

Parallel Streams

customers.parallelStream()
         .forEach(System.out::println);

Use Case

Large data processing
CPU-intensive operations

